article.description: — Myron Amey Jr. had 29 points in San Jose State's 87-82 win over New Orleans on Saturday night.
article.headline: Amey scores 29 to lead San Jose State past New Orleans 87-82
article.linkText: Amey scores 29 to lead San Jose State past New Orleans 87-82
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- — Myron Amey Jr. had 29 points in San Jose State's 87-82 win over New Orleans on Saturday night. Amey had seven rebounds for the Spartans (6-5). Alvaro Cardenas Torre scored 16 points and added 10 assists. Diogo Seixas had 11 points and was 3 of 4 shooting and 5 of 7 from the free throw line. Jordan Johnson led the way for the Privateers (4-5) with 24 points and six assists. Jah Short added 18 points and eight rebounds for New Orleans. In addition, Jamond Vincent had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
